Conditional Statements: 
To make the set of instruction execute only when the given condition is True
used  to declare whether the code has to be executed  or skip based on the given condition
Line - line (sequence)
Condition: An expression that evaluates an result (True or False)
Ex:console.log(5>6)
Block of code: set of instruction . it will execute when the specific condition is True.
Methods
If
If: only one possible condition: 
If the condition is true it will execute other wise it skip
Syntax: 
if(condition){
---block of code
}
Example:
let a= 4
       let b=5
       if(a<b){
        document.write("hello sravan")
       }
Output: hello sravan
 let a= 4
       let b=5
       if(a<b){
        document.write("hello sravan","<br>")
       }
       document.write("brilliant nani")
Output:hello sravan
            brilliant nani
Condition:false

       let a= 4
       let b=5
       if(a>b){
        document.write("hello sravan","<br>")
       }
       document.write("brilliant nani")
       
Output: brilliant nani

If-else
let a=4
       let b=5
       if(a>b){
        document.write("hello sravan","<br>")
       } else{
        document.write("hi chiru","<br>")
       }
       document.write("brilliant chiru")
Output:
hi chiru
brilliant chiru

let age=prompt("Enter your Age?")
       let name=prompt("Enter your Name?")
       if(age<18){
        alert(name+"you are too young to marry")

       }else if(age>35){
         alert(name+"you are too old to marry")
       } else{
        alert(name+"perfect age to marry")
       }
       alert("welcome to my world")

       let a=prompt("enter a score")
       let b=prompt("enter b score")
       let c=a+b
       if((a>300 || b>300)&& (c<500)){
        alert("can team up")

       }else{
        alert("cannot team up")
       }

Switch
Ternary operator



